model <- lmer(kgha ~ trt + (1|rep), data=yield)
anova(model)
## Type III Analysis of Variance Table with Satterthwaite's method
##      Sum Sq Mean Sq NumDF DenDF F value Pr(>F)
## trt 1000248  125031     8    24  1.1048 0.3943
emmip(model, ~ trt) 

lsmeans <- emmeans(model, ~ trt, cont="pairwise", adjust="none", alpha=0.05)

lsmeans

nd <- as.data.frame(lsmeans$emmeans) %>% 
  mutate(trt = factor(trt, levels = c("Controle", "Atectra", "Atectra + Vapor Grip", "Atectra + Roundup Transorb R", "Atectra + Roundup Transorb R + Vapor Grip", "Atectra + Roundup WG", "Atectra + Roundup Original Mais", "Atectra + Roundup Original Mais + Vapor Grip", "Atectra + Roundup Transorb"), labels =c("Controle", "DGA", "DGA + RD", "DGA + Glifosato sal potssico", "DGA + Glifosato sal potssico + RD", "DGA + Glifosato sal de amnio", "DGA + Glifosato sal de di-amnio", "DGA + Glifosato sal de di-amnio + RD", "DGA + Glifosato sal de isopropilamina")))


ggplot(nd, aes(x=trt, y=emmean, color=trt)) + 
geom_point(size=4) + 
  scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0, 6000), breaks=seq(0, 6000, 1000)) +
scale_color_brewer(palette = "Paired") +
theme_bw() + labs(x="", y=expression(bold(paste("Produtividade da soja (kg ha"^"-1",")")))) +
geom_linerange(aes(ymin = lower.CL, ymax = upper.CL), size=1.5) + 
  annotate("text", x = 1, y = 500, label = "P-valor = 0,39", size=5) +
theme(axis.title = element_text(size=16), panel.grid = element_blank(),
axis.text = element_text(size=15, color="black"),
legend.position = "none") +
coord_flip() +
  ggsave("produtividade.png", height=6, width = 10, dpi=600)

Fitotoxicidade

library(ggridges)
fito_1 <- read_csv("injury_14d.csv") %>% 
  pivot_longer(cols = 4:18, names_to = "distance", values_to = "fito") %>% 
  mutate(dat = "14")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   trt = col_character(),
##   trtn = col_double(),

fito_2 <- read_csv("injury_28d.csv") %>% 
  pivot_longer(cols = 4:18, names_to = "distance", values_to = "fito") %>% 
  mutate(dat = "28")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   trt = col_character(),
##   trtn = col_double(),
##   rep = col_double(),
##   `20` = col_double(),
##   `40` = col_double(),

##   `240` = col_double(),
##   `260` = col_double(),
##   `280` = col_double(),
##   `300` = col_double()
## )
fito <- bind_rows(fito_1, fito_2) %>% 
  filter(trtn != "7" & trtn != "11") %>% 
  mutate(trt = factor(trt, levels = c("Controle", "Atectra", "Atectra + Vapor Grip", "Atectra + Roundup Transorb R", "Atectra + Roundup Transorb R + Vapor Grip", "Atectra + Roundup WG", "Atectra + Roundup Original Mais", "Atectra + Roundup Original Mais + Vapor Grip", "Atectra + Roundup Transorb"), labels =c("Controle", "DGA", "DGA + RD", "DGA + Glifosato sal potssico", "DGA + Glifosato sal potssico + RD", "DGA + Glifosato sal de amnio", "DGA + Glifosato sal de di-amnio", "DGA + Glifosato sal de di-amnio + RD", "DGA + Glifosato sal de isopropilamina"))) %>% 
  mutate_if(is.character, as.factor) %>% 
  mutate(dat = factor(dat, levels = c("14", "28"), labels = c("14 DAT", "28 DAT")))
ggplot(fito, aes(y=trt, x=fito, fill=trt)) + #geom_bar(stat="summary", fun.y="mean")
  geom_density_ridges(scale=2) + facet_grid(~dat) +
  labs(x="ndice de fitotoxicidade na soja", y="") + 
  scale_x_continuous(limits = c(1, 10), breaks=seq(1, 10, 1)) +
  scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Set1") + theme_bw() +
  theme(axis.title = element_text(size=14, face="bold"), 
        panel.grid = element_blank(), strip.text = element_text(size=14, face="bold"),
axis.text = element_text(size=12, color="black"),
legend.position = "none") +
  ggsave("fito.png", height=6, width=9, dpi=600)

  group_by(trt, dat) %>% 
  summarise(mean = mean(fito)) %>%
